        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "| Ligand (donor type) | β definition | log K (K1) | T (°C) | I (M) | Notes |\n|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---|\n| Thiocyanate, SCN− (S-donor to Hg) | [M]+[L]⇌[ML] | 9.64 | 25 | 0.0 | Hg–SCN− binds via S to soft Hg2+ |\n| Thiourea, NH2–CS–NH2 (S-donor) | [M]+[L]⇌[ML] | (no ML value at 25 °C, I ≤ 0.2 M retrieved in this pass) | — | — | Hg–(thiourea) forms strong complexes; ML constants commonly reported under different I/media in SRD-46 |\n| Ethylenediamine (en), H2N–CH2–CH2–NH2 (N-donor) | [M]+[L]⇌[ML] | 14.3 | 25 | 0.10 | Bidentate amine; very strong Hg2+–N binding |\n| Ammonia, NH3 (N-donor) | [M]+[L]⇌[ML] | (not returned at 25 °C, I ≤ 0.2 M in this pass) | — | — | SRD‑46 contains Hg–NH3 data at similar conditions; values are lower than for en |\n| Imidazole (N-donor) | [M]+[L]⇌[ML] | (not returned at 25 °C, I ≤ 0.2 M in this pass) | — | — | Hg–imidazole entries exist; generally weaker than en |\n| Pyridine (N-donor) | [M]+[L]⇌[ML] | (not returned at 25 °C, I ≤ 0.2 M in this pass) | — | — | Weaker than en; comparable to imidazole under similar media |\n| Carbonate, HCO3−/CO3^2− (O-donor) | [M]+[L]⇌[ML] | (no ML value at 25 °C, low I, retrieved in this pass) | — | — | Hg–carbonate complexing is weak and often masked by hydrolysis |",
