        "paragraph_index": 4,
        "text": "Summary hypothesis, supported by SRD‑46 examples\n- For monodentate ligands at 25 °C, Hg2+ shows S-donor > N-donor > O-donor preference: e.g., thiocyanate (S-bound) log K1 = 9.64 (25 °C, I = 0) > typical monodentate N donors (NH3, imidazole, pyridine; generally lower than S donors) > carbonate/carboxylates (weak).\n- Chelation amplifies N-donor strength: ethylenediamine (N,N-bidentate) exhibits very high log K1 = 14.3 (25 °C, I = 0.10 M), consistent with the chelate effect rather than intrinsic N > S preference.",
